Software exhibiting fault: !Connect/!Mail     Version:  2.68 beta
       Component at fault:                    Version:                      
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Computer:     RiscPC  OS:    3.70        Monitor:     AKF6x     Ether: No 
     Mem:         34              RelNote status:               Eco: No 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Summary:  !Connect and !Mail "Cancel" Buttons Do Not Cancel        
Synopsis:                                                          
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Details:

MHill (29-Jan-98):

This fault concerns all the dialogue boxes that can be configured by
"Menuing" over the !Connect and !Mail icons on the iconbar.

If you start editing a dialogue box and then change your mind and click on
"Cancel", the "variables" are not returned to their previous values.  Not
only are the new values still displayed if you re-open the dialogue box, but
in some cases the new values have put put into effect (e.g. "Connect when
there are n messages").

The good news is that these new values are not stored when you quit !Connect
and !Mail.


