   1. "Location" menu - no help given.
   2. Start Weekdays - arrows help reversed.
   3. End Weekdays - arrows help reversed.
   4. Text "Disconnect when idle for" - gives help message "HIP52".
   5. Blank space under this text - gives help message "HIP55".

B) Mail
   1. Text "POP3 Address" - gives help message "HMA20".
   2. POP3 Address writable field -gives help message "HMA21".
   3. Text "Protocol" - gives help message "HMA12".
   4. Text "SMTP" - gives help message "HMA13".
   5. Text "POP3" - gives help message "HMA14".

   ....and so on down to "HMA18".

C) Administration
   1. Position mouse pointer about 1.5 inches to the right of the text
      Show detailed log".  Help gives message about servers log window.
      The pointer is so far right, it should display help about the
      window saying "This window lets you configure administration
      options".  Similarly with the other 4 tick-box options in this
      dialogue box.


