Reported by <jonathan@briggs.prestel.co.uk> (Jonathan Briggs) (27-Dec-97):
I have produced a reliable script for the ISP Prestel On Line, to whom should I 
send it ?
If I load !Connect then !Mail with my Mail user name and password and then try 
to Connect.Mail Only (or Mail and news) then the password I have defined as a 
!Mail user is sent to my ISP not my ISP login password. I can not solve this 
problem by using my ISP password as my Mail user password as Prestel INSIST 
on 16 character passwords which users are unable to change and as you know 
!Mail user passwords have a 10 character limit. If instead I load !Connect then 
!Browse instead then all works fine, even if I subsequently load !Mail.
Sent mail does not seem to be saved in a folder similar to incoming mail, for me 
this is an essential feature of any email package.
No progress indication is shown when mail or news is being down/up loaded this 
makes it difficult to know when to disconnect for those of us who have to pay the 
phone bill and where every extra unnecessary second counts.
For the same reason the feature of the news software which makes it download all 
articles automatically from a subscribed newsgroup is for me unacceptable. MS 
Internet News is much better for me as it just downloads the subject of each 
posting and then gives the user the opportunity to decide which articles to 
download. This is done with the threads set to not automatically expand.
Finally !Browse and it's Hotlist are great !!!






