Fault id: PAN-00969   Submitted by:          MHill        Updated: 12-Dec-97
Severity:    Medium      Reference:        MH-0125         Review: No 
Priority:    Medium            FAO:       PGarside        On loan: Yes
State:  Investigate  Repeatability:         Always  Support files: No 
Type:                 Duplicate of:                    Workaround:    
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                   Fixed in:
      Software under test: RPC150             Release:          ?           
Software exhibiting fault: !Connect           Version:       2.62
       Component at fault:                    Version:                      
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Computer:     RiscPC  OS:    3.70        Monitor:     AKF8x     Ether: Yes
     Mem:         41              RelNote status:               Eco: No 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Summary:  If Username and Node name are the same thing then .....  
Synopsis:                                                          
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Details:

MHill (28-Nov-97):

If the service provider gives you a Username, Password, Telephone number,
etc. and then you use !Connect to set it all up, you are suddenly asked for
a "Node name" and think that the provider has forgotten to give you this
information.

So if Username and Node name are the same, change !Connect to ask for the
Username.


MNevilleSmith (01-Dec-97):

FAO CElkins. 

CElkins (01-Dec-93):

These are *not* technically, the same thing, since assignment of a
nodename implies a fixed IP address and DNS record for same.

Suggest a documentation change to reflect usage of !Connect where ISPs are
likely to specify a "Username" rather than a "Node Name", though
alternatively !Connect could be modified as suggested above, and the
documentation changed to reflect where the ISP may specify a nodename as
opposed to a username.

CElkins (03-Dec-93):

!Connect 2.66 has been modified to use the label "Login ID" rather than
either node or username.

The documentation has not yet been modified.

CElkins (11-Dec-93):

Suggest P.Garside address the documentation issue.

